comment: Anderson (NOP) initiates the contact as he leans into Thompson (GSW) who maintains legal guarding position on the jumpshot.
Curry (GSW) does not intentionally kick the ball on the play.
Bogut (GSW) makes contact with Davis' (NOP) body and the contact affects his movement to the basket and shot attempt.
Speights (GSW) wraps up Cunningham (NOP) and makes illegal contact prior to creating a jump ball situation.
Davis (NOP) and Green (GSW) make incidental contact with one another that does not affect Green's layup attempt.
Green (GSW) makes incidental contact with Davis (NOP) as the two players jump for the loose ball.
Evans (NOP) makes body to body contact with Iguodala (GSW) that affects his ability to retrieve and secure the loose ball.
Evans (NOP) and Iguodala (GSW) both dive for the loose ball and make incidental contact with one another.
Evans (NOP) does not push off from Iguodala (GSW) as he gets open for the inbounds pass.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Iguodala (GSW) was upheld.
Iguodala (GSW) reaches in and makes contact with Evans' (NOP) leg and makes foot to foot contact causing him to fall to the floor.
Pondexter (NOP) legally defends Curry's (GSW) floater and allows him to land.
Green (GSW) commits a take foul on Davis (NOP).
Pondexter (NOP) commits a take foul on Curry (GSW).
LHH shows that while Curry (GSW) draws Cunningham (NOP) up, contact occurs after he establishes a legal guarding position on the floor, and after Curry withdraws his shooting attempt.
Curry (GSW) drops the ball after picking up his dribble and is the first player to touch the ball.
